an data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Φιλ\"><span data-text=\"Φιλ\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"\">Φιλ̣</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></span></span>  <br id=\"al5-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">5</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"νίδας  Ἡρα\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"νίδας\">[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.</span><span data-text=\"νίδας\" data-n=\"75\" data-lemma=\"\">νίδας</span></span>  <span dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)</span>  <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἡρα\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Ἡρα\"><span data-text=\"Ἡρα\" data-n=\"80\" data-lemma=\"\">Ἡρα</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></span></span>  <br id=\"al6-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">6</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"στοκλῆς  Πο\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"στοκλῆς\">[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span data-text=\"στοκλῆς\" data-n=\"95\" data-lemma=\"\">στοκλῆς</span></span>  <span dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)</span>  <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Πο\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Πο\"><span data-text=\"Πο\" data-n=\"100\" data-lemma=\"\">Πο</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></span></span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag, 2014-09-11, cass. 6, magazzino B, MARPO</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"ντος\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"ντος\"><span data-text=\"ντος\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"\">ΝΤΟΣ</span></span></span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"ς  Φιλι\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"ς\">[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span data-text=\"ς\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"\">Σ</span></span> &nbsp;&nbsp; <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Φιλι\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Φιλι\"><span data-text=\"Φιλι\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"\">ΦΙΛ.</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></span></span><br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"ίδας  Φιλ\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"ίδας\">[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·</span><span data-text=\"ίδας\" data-n=\"55\" data-lemma=\"\">ΙΔΑΣ</span></span> &nbsp;&nbsp; <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Φιλ\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Φιλ\"><span data-text=\"Φιλ\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"\">ΦΙ.</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></span></span><br id=\"al5-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">5</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"νίδας  Ἡρα\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"νίδας\">[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·</span><span data-text=\"νίδας\" data-n=\"75\" data-lemma=\"\">ΝΙΔΑΣ</span></span> &nbsp;&nbsp; <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἡρα\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Ἡρα\"><span data-text=\"Ἡρα\" data-n=\"80\" data-lemma=\"\">ΗΡΑ</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></span></span><br id=\"al6-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">6</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"στοκλῆς  Πο\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"στοκλῆς\">[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span data-text=\"στοκλῆς\" data-n=\"95\" data-lemma=\"\">ΣΤΟΚΛΗΣ</span></span> &nbsp;&nbsp; <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Πο\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Πο\"><span data-text=\"Πο\" data-n=\"100\" data-lemma=\"\">ΠΟ</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></span></span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic001035_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\" src=\"ISic001035_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001035.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\" src=\"ISic001035-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic001035_rear_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\" src=\"ISic001035_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001035_rear.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\" src=\"ISic001035_rear-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>Text from autopsy</span></span>; </li><li><span class=\"1\">1: <span>Not noted in previous editions</span></span><br></li><li><span class=\"3\">3: <span>Pugliese Carratelli: -].Σ ΦΙΛ[-</span></span><br></li><li><span class=\"4\">4: <span>Orsi, Kaibel: -]ΙΔΑΣ ΦΙΛ[-</span></span><br></li><li><span class=\"5\">5: <span>Orsi, Kaibel: -]ΝΙΔΑΣ ΗΡΑ[-; Pugliese Carratelli: -]Ι̣ΝΙΛΑΣ ΗΡΑ[-</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2> translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">  </p><p>  </p></div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>As noted already by Orsi (with Halbherr), this is a list of names. In lines 3-6, a name in the nominative is separated by one letter space from what is presumably the associated patronymic (in the genitive). In line 2, the letters ΝΤΟΣ are set somewhat further to the right than the names below, but a longer name in the nominative ending in -ντος seems the most likely resolution (since a singular genitive participle referring to e.g. office held, or activity undertaken hardly fits with a list of nominative names below). It is clear that the gap between names is in no way aligned from one line to the next. Kaibel included the text in the addenda to IG XIV, and there proposed that it should be connected to another fragment with nominative names, also from Akrai, and in Palermo museum (<a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001034\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001034</a>), although he noted in his commentary that his description of the latter was clearly flawed, if this was the case. Pugliese Carratelli merely noted the proposal without judgement, but as Manni Piraino observes, the piece presented here is of marble, while the Palermo fragment is of the local limestone (Kaibel should have trusted his original notes!), and the two cannot be part of the same stone. A closer parallel from Akrai is offered by a fragment recording gymnasiarchs (<a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001033\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001033</a>. Several similar marble fragments with names are preserved from Hellenistic Syracuse also. (Note that IGPalermo misreports the inventory number as 657.)</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li>  <a href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">214a</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</a>  </li><li> Orsi NSA 1889 389 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392</a>  </li><li> Pugliese Carratelli 1956 no.4 tav.34 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001394\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001394</a>  </li><li> Manni Piraino 1973 pp.56-57 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000531\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000531</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"><p>Moderately regular thinly incised letters with pronounced terminal serifs, and a fairly square module. Alpha with straight bar; delta (and sigma) show slight curvature; kappa with short arms; omicron slightly smaller (c.2mm less) and above the line; sigma with parallel outer strokes, and sometimes a pronounced extension to the mid-join; phi with extended vertical (11mm) and small over-semi-circular loops.</p> Line 1-6  5-8  Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
